opened: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/bmcweb/+/57442

Marking this comment resolved, and following up on the review.
version is not a string now?
I didn't understand the question, but it seems like you answered it.  Let me know if I can clarify anything.
This needs looked at in more detail...... json schema has abstract classes now?

Need to poll the folks looking at this review for a sec;  We need a way to compare version numbers, and every option I can find has some compromise.  The options that I can find are:

1. https://pypi.org/project/packaging/ version.parse.  That's what the current patchset does, but requires a python dependency that isn't installed by default, so that needs added to the build script.
2. distutils.LooseVersion.  Installed by default, so keeps our dependencies down, but gives a warning on using it that distutils is being deprecated soon.
3. Write/copy our own function.  No dependencies, but requires us to maintain more code.


What do folks think is the right answer here?

1 or 2. I would prefer we not write our own if there is already solutions out there that works. 

Between 1 or 2, I think I would prefer 1, I think it is reasonable we add that packaging python dependency to the build scripts and require it for anyone running this script locally. It seems widely used and exactly what we want? 

Random Googling seems to indicate movement away from distutils.LooseVersion so I don't think we should use it.  
https://github.com/Azure/azure-cli/issues/17170

I vote 1.
Requires https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc-build-scripts/+/57434 to be merged to build
